&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen with our CAMHS Generic Team. We are looking for an enthusiastic and inspirational qualified nurse or qualified social worker who is committed to improving the lives of children, young people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expected to complete robust assessment and plan and deliver excellent standards of care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An integral team member of a busy team so team working skills are essential as well as the ability to work independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing your skills in a specialist area of practice and there will be future opportunities for CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short Listing Date 19th and 20th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date 30th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandra Simpson, Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sandra.simpson@bdct.nhs.uk / 07740 422650&lt;/p&gt;
